# Strings üßµ

Strings store text. Use single or double quotes.

```javascript
let carName1 = "Volvo XC60";
let carName2 = 'Volvo XC60';
```

You can use properties like `.length`:
```javascript
let txt = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ";
let len = txt.length;
```

